If they ſay,§ 2. that an argument out of Scripture is ſufficient ground of Divine faith, why are they ſo offended with the Proteſtants for beleiving every part of their Religion upon that ground, upon which they build all theirs at once? and if following the ſame Rule with equall deſire of finding the truth by it, (having neither of thoſe qualities, which Iſidorus Peluſiota ſayes, are the cauſes of all Hereſies; 
                  〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
               , Pride and Prejudication) why ſhould God be more offended with the one then the other, though they chance to erre?
